init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Upon calling the number, you find yourself in an abandoned warehouse.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're on a balcony overlooking a sprawling city.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You then hear someone clearing their throat behind you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: a man with a cowboy hat, dressed in a suit.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: removes his hat and introduces himself as "Agent Dale Cooper.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Agent Cooper explains that you have been chosen to be the new Truman.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are to solve the mystery of who is murdering people in this city.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Agent Cooper explains that in order to get you acquainted with the city, he's going to give you a tour.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He explains that this city is called "Twin Peaks".

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You will have 8 days for each season.
